      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agent): infer agent from fresh session keys",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #89746.\n\nGateway `agent` requests that supplied a fresh explicit session key such as `agent:main:probe-*` could reach dispatch without carrying the agent id embedded in the key. Existing session resolution could still create the session row, but the dispatch path did not consistently preserve the key's agent owner for a never-before-seen session.\n\nThis change infers the configured agent id from well-formed agent-prefixed session keys before gateway dispatch, while preserving the existing validation behavior for global-scope aliases and unknown non-global keys.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Infer `agentId` from `agent:<id>:<key>` when `<id>` is a configured agent and no explicit `agentId` was supplied.\n- Keep the existing selected-global unknown-agent rejection behavior.\n- Add a regression test proving a fresh explicit session key is persisted and dispatched with the key's agent id.\n\n## Public surface\n\nNo public config options, plugin APIs, or protocol fields are added or changed.\n\n## Proof\n\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.gateway.config.ts src/gateway/server-methods/agent.test.ts`\n  - `290 passed`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --engine codex --codex-bin /home/giodl/.local/toolchains/node-v22.22.3-linux-x64/bin/codex --parallel-tests \"OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.gateway.config.ts src/gateway/server-methods/agent.test.ts\"`\n  - `autoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported`\n  - tests exit `0`",
        "branch": "fix-fresh-agent-session",
